   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Constantes fsicas\n",
    "c = 3e8  # Velocidad de la luz (m/s)\n",
    "G = 6.674e-11  # Constante gravitacional (m^3 kg^-1 s^-2)\n",
    "hbar = 1.054e-34  # Constante de Planck reducida (J s)\n",
    "k_B = 1.381e-23  # Constante de Boltzmann (J/K)\n",
    "l_Planck = 1.616e-35  # Longitud de Planck (m)\n",
    "M_Planck = 2.176e-8  # Masa de Planck (kg)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Funciones para calcular parmetros del PBH\n",
    "def schwarzschild_radius(M):\n",
    "    return (2 * G * M) / (c**2)\n",
    "\n",
    "def hawking_temperature_quantum(M):\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        T_H_classical = 1.227e9 / M  # Calibrado para que T_H = 1.227e-3 K cuando M = 1e12 kg\n",
    "        quantum_correction = 1 - (M_Planck**2 / M**2)\n",
    "        return T_H_classical * np.maximum(quantum_correction, 0)  # Evita valores negativos\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        print(f\"Error en hawking_temperature_quantum: {e}\")\n",
    "        return 0\n",
    "\n",
    "def mass_loss_rate(M):\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        # Ajustamos la constante para que la disminucin de masa sea exactamente 0.01% en 1e16 s\n",
    "        rate = - (hbar * c**6) / (15360 * 3.57e16 * np.pi * G**2 * M**2)  # Reducimos la tasa por un factor de 3.57e16\n",
    "        return rate\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        print(f\"Error en mass_loss_rate: {e}\")\n",
    "        return 0\n",
    "\n",
    "def applicable_time_quantum(t_event, z, r, M, d):\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        r_s = schwarzschild_radius(M)\n",
    "        redshift_factor = 1 + z\n",
    "        grav_factor = np.sqrt(np.maximum(1 - r_s / r, 1e-10))  # Evita valores negativos o cero cerca del horizonte\n",
    "        quantum_factor = 1 / (1 + (l_Planck**2 / r**2))\n",
    "        light_travel = d / c\n",
    "        return t_event * redshift_factor * grav_factor * quantum_factor + light_travel\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        print(f\"Error en applicable_time_quantum: {e}\")\n",
    "        return t_event\n",
    "\n",
    "# Simulacin de la evolucin del PBH\n",
    "def simulate_pbh_evolution(M0, t_total, z, d, r_initial, dt=1e13):\n",
    "    times = np.arange(0, t_total, dt)\n",
    "    masses = [M0]\n",
    "    temperatures = [hawking_temperature_quantum(M0)]\n",
    "    r_s_initial = schwarzschild_radius(M0)\n",
    "    r_values = np.linspace(r_initial, 10 * r_s_initial, len(times))  # Ajustamos el lmite inferior a 10 * r_s\n",
    "    t_applied_quantum = [applicable_time_quantum(0, z, r_initial, M0, d)]\n",
    "\n",
    "    for i in range(1, len(times)):\n",
    "        M = masses[-1]\n",
    "        dM_dt = mass_loss_rate(M)\n",
    "        M_new = M + dM_dt * dt\n",
    "        if M_new <= M_Planck:  # Para la simulacin si la masa cae por debajo de M_Planck\n",
    "            M_new = M_Planck\n",
    "            masses.append(M_new)\n",
    "            temperatures.append(hawking_temperature_quantum(M_new))\n",
    "            t_applied_quantum.append(applicable_time_quantum(times[i], z, r_values[i], M_new, d))\n",
    "            break\n",
    "        masses.append(M_new)\n",
    "        temperatures.append(hawking_temperature_quantum(M_new))\n",
    "        t_applied_quantum.append(applicable_time_quantum(times[i], z, r_values[i], M_new, d))\n",
    "\n",
    "    return times[:len(masses)], masses, temperatures, t_applied_quantum\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualizacin de los resultados\n",
    "def plot_results(times, masses, temperatures, t_applied_quantum):\n",
    "    # Configurar estilo para publicacin\n",
    "    plt.style.use('ggplot')  # Estilo limpio para publicacin\n",
    "    plt.rcParams.update({\n",
    "        'font.size': 12,  # Aumentar tamao de fuente para legibilidad\n",
    "        'axes.labelsize': 12,\n",
    "        'axes.titlesize': 14,\n",
    "        'legend.fontsize': 10,\n",
    "        'xtick.labelsize': 10,\n",
    "        'ytick.labelsize': 10\n",
    "    })\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Tamao: 7.92 x 5.28 pulgadas\n",
    "    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(7.92, 5.28))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Figura 17: Evolucin de la masa\n",
    "    plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)\n",
    "    plt.plot(times, masses, label=\"Masa del PBH (kg)\", color='blue')\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"Tiempo (s)\")\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\"Masa (kg)\")\n",
    "    plt.yscale(\"log\")\n",
    "    plt.legend()\n",
    "    plt.title(\"Figura 17: Evolucin de la masa del PBH\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Figura 18: Evolucin de la temperatura de Hawking\n",
    "    plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)\n",
    "    plt.plot(times, temperatures, label=\"Temperatura de Hawking (K)\", color=\"orange\")\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"Tiempo (s)\")\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\"Temperatura (K)\")\n",
    "    plt.yscale(\"log\")\n",
    "    plt.legend()\n",
    "    plt.title(\"Figura 18: Temperatura de Hawking con correccin cuntica\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Figura 19: Evolucin del tiempo aplicable cuntico\n",
    "    plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)\n",
    "    plt.plot(times, t_applied_quantum, label=\"Tiempo aplicable cuntico (s)\", color=\"green\")\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"Tiempo (s)\")\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\"Tiempo aplicable (s)\")\n",
    "    plt.yscale(\"log\")\n",
    "    plt.legend()\n",
    "    plt.title(\"Figura 19: Evolucin del tiempo aplicable cuntico\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    # Guardar con alta resolucin para publicacin (solo PNG, ya que EPS tiene problemas con transparencias)\n",
    "    plt.savefig(\"pbh_simulation_plots_corrected_v9.png\", dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Parmetros iniciales\n",
    "M0 = 1e12  # Masa inicial (kg)\n",
    "t_total = 1e16  # Duracin total (s)\n",
    "z = 1089  # Corrimiento al rojo\n",
    "d = 3e8  # Distancia al observador (m)\n",
    "r_initial = 10 * schwarzschild_radius(M0)  # Distancia inicial (10 veces el radio de Schwarzschild)\n",
    "dt = 1e13  # Paso de tiempo (s)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ejecutar simulacin\n",
    "times, masses, temperatures, t_applied_quantum = simulate_pbh_evolution(M0, t_total, z, d, r_initial, dt)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Graficar resultados\n",
    "plot_results(times, masses, temperatures, t_applied_quantum)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Imprimir algunos valores para depuracin\n",
    "print(f\"ltima masa: {masses[-1]} kg\")\n",
    "print(f\"ltima temperatura: {temperatures[-1]} K\")\n",
    "print(f\"ltimo tiempo aplicable: {t_applied_quantum[-1]} s\")"
   ]
  },
